flowRoot.flowPara: Be sure turn printer off and allow it to cool before interacting with heated areas.
Burns may occur if you touch the printing tip or heated plate.
Avoid kickback by using riving knife, anti-kickback pawls, sled or featherboard. Don't use your miter gauge and fence together. Cross cut long boards on miter saw.
Material kicked back may strike person behind saw and cause injury.
Check the laser cutter page on website for instructions on how to identify safe materials.
Laser cutting some materials can release toxic and corrosive fumes.
You can use the "pause" feature to stop the job for a few minutes if you need to leave the room.
Laser cutters can start fires at unpredictable times.

flowRoot.flowPara: Any material or project without a clear name and date is considered trash.

Member only use of powertools.
There is a dumpster on Crown Street past Cafe 9. Use the key in the kitchen window to open. More bags on bathroom shelf.
Dishes left behind make the sink more difficult to use for the next person.
Any guest of a member must have a waiver on file.
Paper waiver are avalible at the door.
Any member can claim one bin.
Full name must be on bin.
Ending membership forfits contents left in bin.
